{"word":"στίξ","slug":"στίξ","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>στίξ</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:στείχω'><el>στείχω</el></a>\n<br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b>the other cases are taken from <a href='S:στίχος'><el>στίχος</el></a>\n<p/><i>a row, line, rank</i> or <i>file</i>, <a href='S:especially'>esp.</a> of soldiers, <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a>:—<a href='S:metaphorically'>metaph.</a>, <el>ἐπέων στίχες</el> <i>verses, lays</i>, <b><a href='S:Pindar'>Pind.</a></b><p/>"}]}